        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 1:57PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
El Huerfano Trading Post, or 20 miles south of Bloomfield, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
El Huerfano Trading Post and Blanco Trading Post.

This includes Highway 550 between Mile Markers 119 and 138.
</description>
        <instruction>Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
